# Future-Proof Component Mapping Standard (v1.2.0)

Source of truth: `project/src/theme/themeCategoryMapping.ts`
Monochrome depth ladder: `project/src/theme/themeMonochromeDepthProtocol.ts` (v2.0.0)
Layout / overflow: `project/src/theme/themeLayoutProtocol.ts`

## Permanent Settings/Profile rule

Whenever creating, editing, or rendering code inside **Settings** or **Profile**, do not use arbitrary colors or sharp edges. Auto-classify elements into the black-to-gray monochromatic depth stack and enforce uniform `rounded-xl` / `rounded-2xl` plus `border border-white/10` on container frames.

Scope DOM with `SETTINGS_PROFILE_SCOPE_ATTR` (`data-settings-profile-scope`). CSS auto-binds Cat 5 text and Cat 4 inputs in `index.css`.

## Monochrome depth stack (default dark)

| Level | Role | Tailwind ref | CSS variable | Tokens |
|-------|------|--------------|--------------|--------|
| L1 | Master accordion / Cat 6 + orange-zone canvas | `bg-neutral-950` | `--main-card-surface-bg` | `themeCardLgClass`, `MasterCategoryPanel` |
| L2 | Sub-category wrapper / Cat 7 | `bg-neutral-900` | `--color-sub-cards` | `SubCategorySectionCard`, `subCardNestedSectionCapsuleClass` |
| L3 | Inner panels, grids, forms | `bg-zinc-800` | `--color-depth-inner` | `surfacePanelClass`, `subCardSmClass`, `subCardGridCellClass` |
| Cat 4 | Inputs, dropdowns, toggles (off) | `bg-zinc-900` | `--surface-input-bg` | `surfaceInputClass`, `monochromeToggleTrackOffClass` |
| Cat 5 | All typography | `text-white` | `--typography-primary` | `typography*Class`, `themeText*Class` |

**Orange Zone:** expanded L1 gap canvas stays Cat 6 (`MasterCategoryPanelBody`, `SubCardNestedStack variant="capsuleOnMain"`). L2/L3 capsules float on top.

## Required workflow for new UI

1. Build a `ThemeClassificationHint` for the element.
2. Call `classifyThemeCategory(hint)` or consult `MONOCHROME_DEPTH_COMPONENT_MAP`.
3. Apply tokens from `getThemeStyleTokens(category)` â€” `actionButtonStyles.ts` or `themeSurfaceStyles.ts`.
4. Tag outermost node: `themeCategoryProps(category)` â†’ `data-theme-category`.
5. Settings/Profile routes: add `SETTINGS_PROFILE_SCOPE_ATTR` on page root.

## Classification priority (first match wins)

1. `excludedFromTheming` â†’ auth sign-up static only
2. Page root â†’ `page`
3. Outer layout / modal backing â†’ `mainCard`
4. Nested inside master (accordion, list row) â†’ `subCard`
5. Form control / input tag â†’ `filter`
6. Typography tag â†’ `text`
7. Navigation-only â†’ `nav`
8. Primary mutation â†’ `primary`
9. Utility / currency tool â†’ `currency`
10. Generic `button` â†’ `nav`
11. Default â†’ `text`

## Forbidden

- Hardcoded `bg-violet-*`, `bg-emerald-*`, `bg-indigo-*`, `bg-gray-*` on Settings/Profile structural wrappers.
- Same hex on nested L1 + L2 + L3 (visual bleed).
- Sharp corners on depth-layer frames.
- Skipping perimeter `border` on depth containers.
- `themeCategoryProps('subCard')` on `MasterCategoryPanel` (must be `mainCard`).
- Non-white default typography on dark monochrome surfaces.
- Cat 4 inputs using L3 gray in default dark mode.

## Persistence (dual channel)

- Registered: Firebase via `settingsPersistenceEngine` / `userFirebaseSync`
- Guest: isolated localStorage keys (`guest_theme_preferences`, etc.)
- Dynamic switches in Settings/Profile must route through `LanguageContext` + `useSettingsPersistence`
